dismissalComment.html: Tamim's frustration gets the better of him! Good length ball outside the off stump. Tamim jumps down the track and looks to loft it away. dismissalText.commentary: Tom Latham run out (Rubel Hossain) 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: on the leg stump. Taylor turns it to square-leg and for a moment wants the second. Latham, though, is quicker than he expects him to be and is half way down the pitch. dismissalText.commentary: Tim Southee b Mashrafe Mortaza 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 0

commentTextItems.html: fuller ball on the off stump. Southee looks to defend it and is beaten. The ball hits the top of off stump. Second series win for Bangladesh over New Zealand

commentPostTextItems.html: And that's the series for Bangladesh. New Zealand were in trouble from the time they lost Devcich. They lost Devcich and Elliot in two balls, Brendon McCullum and Latham in the space of three balls.
Spinners of Bangladesh created the pressure and strangulated the run scoring opportunities. Though Taylor continued to stay at the wicket, he didn't look dangerous.
Tamim, Mominul and Rahim- all of them struggled,  but they managed a few runs between them. The partnership between Gazi and Mahmudullah allowed them to come back into the game.
Batting of New Zealand leaves a lot to be desired and they need to turn it around in the next game

Brendon McCullum, New Zealand captain, says, "We gave ourselves a real opportunity to chase the total down, but credit to Bangladesh that they played better cricket than us. We are having a rough time as a unit. Congratulations to Bangladesh"
Rahim, Bangladesh captain says,"We were 20 runs short on this track. We needed a good opening partnership. It wasn't an easy track to bat on. Tamim deserves all the credit for staying there"
Sohag Gazi is the man of the match for his all round performance.
That's it from all of us here. Do join us for the 3rd ODI. Till then it's a good night from all of us here

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal b Anderson 58 (86b 5x4 1x6 129m) SR: 67.44

dismissalComment.html: Tamim's frustration gets the better of him! Good length ball outside the off stump. Tamim jumps down the track and looks to loft it away. This time he gets an inside edge and see's the stumps rearranged. That's poor batting from Tamim- he allowed the frustration of not scoring boundaries get to him and it ultimately led to his dismissal

headshotImage.caption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c †Latham b Neesham 31 (28b 1x4 2x6 56m) SR: 110.71

dismissalComment.html: and that's the wicket! Rahim skips down the track and looks to loft it away. He gets an outside edge that Latham takes by just moving his hands to the right

headshotImage.caption: Naeem Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Naeem Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Naeem Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Naeem Islam player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Naeem Islam c †Latham b Mills 16 (19b 1x4 1x6 33m) SR: 84.21

dismissalComment.html: Naeem decides to chase a short ball on the leg stump line. He had no option left as he had shuffled across before the bowler could bowl. He only manages to get some glove on it and has to depart. Bangladesh's innings is coming undone in the powerplay overs

headshotImage.caption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Hossain c BB McCullum b Neesham 3 (6b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: that's the third wicket in the batting powerplay! Fuller ball outside the off stump. Nasir lofts it and doesn't get enough power on the stroke to propel it over long-off. McCullum manning the long-off area runs back a few steps and takes an easy catch

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah c & b Anderson 21 (26b 1x4 0x6 41m) SR: 80.76

dismissalComment.html: short ball. Mahmudullah, for some reason, charges down the track and looks to pull it. All he gets is a top edge and that's an easy offering for the bowler

headshotImage.caption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza b Neesham 14 (8b 2x4 1x6 8m) SR: 175

dismissalComment.html: looks to guide it to third-man, misses and finds his off stump pegged back

headshotImage.caption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sohag Gazi c Devcich b Anderson 26 (24b 1x4 1x6 45m) SR: 108.33

dismissalComment.html: short ball. Gazi makes room and looks to cut it. He does, but straight into the hands of the fielder at  point

headshotImage.caption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: James Neesham player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rubel Hossain b Neesham 2 (7b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: and Bangladesh can't play out the fifty overs as Rubel is beaten all ends up by the yorker.

headshotImage.caption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Anton Devcich c & b Sohag Gazi 19 (44b 2x4 0x6 57m) SR: 43.18

dismissalComment.html: playing for the turn when there isn't any! He tamely taps it back to the bowler who takes the catch and has some words and shows the way to the pavilion! A good catch and a timely wicket

headshotImage.caption: Hamish Rutherford player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Hamish Rutherford player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Hamish Rutherford player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Hamish Rutherford player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hamish Rutherford b Mashrafe Mortaza 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: and that's the early wicket that Bangladesh were looking for! Rutherford takes a huge stride forward and looks to smash the ball away. All that he manages is an inside edge back onto the stumps

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Grant Elliott lbw b Abdur Razzak 14 (32b 0x4 0x6 48m) SR: 43.75

dismissalComment.html: two wickets in two balls then ! A fuller ball on the middle stump. Elliot looks to defend it and is beaten by the ball that straightens a touch after pitching. That's plumb. Brilliant bit of bowling that from Razzak. New Zealand have to do all the running in this game

headshotImage.caption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor c Mahmudullah b Sohag Gazi 45 (82b 2x4 1x6 124m) SR: 54.87

dismissalComment.html: no, he isn't ! Gazi flights the ball outside the off stump. Taylor lofts it straight into the hands of Mahmudullah at long-on.

dismissalText.commentary: Corey Anderson c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Mashrafe Mortaza 37 (40b 5x4 1x6 59m) SR: 92.5

dismissalComment.html: and that's the wicket! Corey chases a wide delivery and edges it. Rahim dives to his left and pulls off a screamer. He throws the ball up and seems to have done his shoulder some harm

dismissalText.commentary: Brendon McCullum lbw b Mominul Haque 14 (18b 1x4 0x6 31m) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: good length ball on the off stump. McCullum looks to defend it and moves across. The ball beats the outside edge and hits him on the back pad. Bangladesh might consider themselves lucky that they have his wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Tom Latham run out (Rubel Hossain) 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: on the leg stump. Taylor turns it to square-leg and for a moment wants the second. Latham, though, is quicker than he expects him to be and is half way down the pitch. Rahim collects the throw and whips the bails off before Latham can get back to the crease. Bangladesh's match to lose from here on
